   <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#aphrodite"><name nymRef="#Ἀφροδίτη"><unclear>Ἀ</unclear>φ<supplied reason="lost">ρ</supplied><unclear>ο</unclear>δί<unclear>τ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ῃ</supplied></name></persName> <w lemma="ὅς">ὃν</w> <w lemma="ἐπαγγέλλω">ἐπηνγίλ<unclear>α</unclear>το</w>  <persName type="attested" ref="http://www.lgpn.ox.ac.uk/id/V5b-3235"><name nymRef="#Ἀρτεμίδωρος">Ἀρτεμίδω<unclear>ρ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ος</supplied></name>  <persName type="attested" ref="http://www.lgpn.ox.ac.uk/id/V5b-2411"><name nymRef="#Ἀπολλώνιος "><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπολλωνίου</supplied></name></persName></persName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>l. 1,  Perhaps <foreign xml:lang="grc">θεᾷ</foreign> at the end</p>
            <p>l. 2,  The name of the goddess was probably erased in the Christian period.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Artemidoros son of Artemidoros the son of Apol[lonios] to Aphrodite <note rend="italic" place="not specified" xml:lang=""/> [the goddess] Aphrodite, (the statuary) which Artemidoros [?son of Apollonios] promised.</p>
         </div>
